    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is no text-object which applies to the entire buffer. To apply an operator to an entire buffer you currently need to do something like `ggVG`, which moves the cursor. This makes it inconvenient to, for example, yank or format an entire buffer.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIntroduce a default text-object for the entire buffer.\n\n[Discussed on Matrix here](https://matrix.to/#/!cylwlNXSwagQmZSkzs:matrix.org/$W3yEAapnfS2D_Da65WnRSKFJSnXp_ls7GEc3c2sjHAM?via=mozilla.org&via=matrix.org&via=gitter.im). Suggested keymaps that were proposed where `al` (for all lines) and `<CR>` (just kinda feels right imo).",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I suggest e.\n\nhttps://github.com/kana/vim-textobj-entire\n\nhas been around for a while.\n\nI haven't worked with textobjects - would be down to write a draft for this.\n",
