            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I vote against `e` because that's already a useful motion (for example `gUe` to capitalize the rest of the word). I dont necessarily think `<CR>` is ideal, but that is at least somewhat superfluous with `j`.\n\nHere's the snippet I posted on matrix you can use as a jumping off point if you want. It restores cursor position and doesn't pollute the jumplist:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set(\"o\", \"<CR>\", function()\n  local pos = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)\n  vim.cmd(\"keepj norm! gg\" .. vim.v.operator .. \"G\")\n  vim.api.nvim_win_set_cursor(0, pos)\nend)\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-04-19T10:20:53Z",
