            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I use `ag` since it's easy to remember, thanks to `gg` and `G`. It also keeps `l` free for something else, which is useful since many words start with `l`.\n\nThere are only two issues with `ag`:\n\n1. I need to remap `gqga` to `gqag` because I sometimes mistype that combination.\n2. I have no idea what `ig` can be used for. It could just be the same as `ag` for now.\n\nBut `al` and `il` are also great choices. At least not `ae`.",
