        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I use `i_` and `a_`\n\n- While not a mnemonic per se, it is in line with `_` and `g_`\n- `a_` is a big selection that I don't want to be making by accident\n- I don't use `i_` that much, so I don't want it taking up more commonly used real estate.\n\n> I humbly suggest `ad` for document or `af` for file: mnemonic and avoids the inconsistency of \"all lines\" instead of \"around lines\". Whether there can be a useful distinction between `id` and `ad`, such that the former deserves to be implemented, would be up for debate.\n\nDoesn't matter *that* much, but `ad` and `af` are what treesitter-textobjects uses in its documentation for conditional and function call. The function call object is quite useful.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-20T15:43:07Z",
